cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on privacy concerns and proposes a solution using Local Differential Privacy (LDP) to protect image data. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with image data and proposes a supervised image feature extractor for image classification. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the impact of perturbation on data utility regarding count-based and distance-based machine learning algorithms. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a method to locally perturb image representation before revealing it to the data user. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image data and proposes a method for privacy-preserving image classification.
